        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 30 at 3:24PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 323 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Choctaw, or 7 miles south of Clinton, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Heber Springs...                  Clinton...
Fairfield Bay...                  Greers Ferry...
Quitman...                        Damascus...
Higden...                         Fairfield Bay Marina...
Fairbanks...                      Whipple...
Sugar Loaf Recreation Area...     Choctaw...
Bee Branch...                     Austin in Conway County...
Brownsville...                    Formosa...
Hopewell in Cleburne County...    Pearson...
Narrows Marina...                 Choctow Recreation Area...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
